{"id":474259,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Addison","text":"Thomas Addison (April 1793 \u2013 29 June 1860) was an English physician and scientist.\nAddison was born in Longbenton, Northumberland. He discovered Addison's disease and Addison's anemia.\nAddison killed himself in Brighton, East Sussex. He jumped from a hospital he worked in. He suffered from depression.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"English_people","surface_form":"English","offset":50},{"uri":"Physician","surface_form":"physician","offset":58},{"uri":"Scientist","surface_form":"scientist","offset":72},{"uri":"Longbenton","surface_form":"Longbenton","offset":103},{"uri":"Northumberland","surface_form":"Northumberland","offset":115},{"uri":"Addison%27s_disease","surface_form":"Addison's disease","offset":145},{"uri":"Pernicious_anemia","surface_form":"Addison's anemia","offset":167},{"uri":"Suicide","surface_form":"killed himself","offset":193},{"uri":"Brighton","surface_form":"Brighton","offset":211},{"uri":"East_Sussex","surface_form":"East Sussex","offset":221},{"uri":"Hospital","surface_form":"hospital","offset":251},{"uri":"Depression_(mood)","surface_form":"depression","offset":291}]}